<subSubSection pageId="50" pageNumber="51" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="50.[151,1436,152,858]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,330,751,777]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">Etymology</emphasis>
. From Egyptian mythology, Hapi was one of the four sons of Horus. He protected the canopic jars containing the embalmed lungs of the deceased. It is a noun in apposition.
</paragraph>
